terms.medium_def:
A man living at the time before the Flood, first mentioned at Gen.5.12; 
referred to as Mahalalel (מַהֲלַלְאֵל), or Mahalaleel (NIV= Mahalel) (Μαλελεήλ); 
a son of Kenan; 
father of Jared.

A man living before Israel's Monarchy, first mentioned at Jdg.12.13; 
only referred to as Hillel (הִלֵּל); 
father of Abdon. § a native of Pirathon in Mount Ephraim, the father of Abdon the judge

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.4.16; 
only referred to as Jehallelel (יְהַלֶּלְאֵל); 
father of Ziph, Ziphah, Tiria, Asarel.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 2Ch.29.12; 
only referred to as Jehallelel (יְהַלֶּלְאֵל); 
father of Azariah.

A man living at the time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at Neh.11.4; 
only referred to as Mahalalel (מַהֲלַלְאֵל); 
father of Shephatiah.

A Singer from the tribe of Levi living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.6.44; 
referred to as Jeduthun or Jeduthun (=Qere. Ketiv= Jedithun) (יְדוּתוּן), or Ethan (אֵיתָן); 
a son of Kishi; 
father of Obed-edom, Mattithiah, Gedaliah, Zeri, Jeshaiah, Hashabiah, Shemaiah and Uzziel. § a Levite of the family of Merari and the chief of one of the 3 choirs of the temple whose descendants also formed one of the perpetual temple choirs; he is named at the beginning of 3 Psalms (Ps 39:1; 62:1; 77: either as the composer or the recipient of those Psalms but most likely as the leader of the choir by which those Psalms were to be sung

A man from the tribe of Levi living at the time of Exile and Return, first mentioned at 1Ch.9.16; 
referred to as Jeduthun or Jeduthun (=Qere. Ketiv= Jedithun) (יְדוּתוּן); 
father of Galal. § a Levite of the family of Merari and the chief of one of the 3 choirs of the temple whose descendants also formed one of the perpetual temple choirs; he is named at the beginning of 3 Psalms (Ps 39:1; 62:1; 77: either as the composer or the recipient of those Psalms but most likely as the leader of the choir by which those Psalms were to be sung

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.3.24; 
referred to as Hodaviah (הוֹדַוְיָה), or Hodaiah (=Ketiv) (הוֹדַיְוָהוּ); 
son of Elioenai; 
a brother of Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan, Delaiah and Anani.

A man living at the time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at 1Ch.9.7; 
only referred to as Hodaviah (הוֹדַוְיָה); 
a son of Hassenuah; 
father of Meshullam.

A man from the tribe of Simeon(?) living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.4.37; 
only referred to as Jedaiah (יְדָיָה); 
a son of Shimri; 
father of Allon.

A man living at the time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at Neh.3.10; 
only referred to as Jedaiah (יְדָיָה); 
a son of Harumaph.

A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, only mentioned at Gen.22.22; 
only referred to as Jidlaph (יִדְלָ֑ף); 
son of Nahor and Milcah; 
a brother of Uz, Buz, Kemuel, Chesed, Hazo, Pildash and Bethuel; 
half-brother of: Tebah, Gaham, Tahash and Maacah. § a son of Nahor

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.3.24; 
referred to as Hodaviah (הוֹדַוְיָה), or Hodaiah (=Ketiv) (הוֹדַיְוָהוּ); 
son of Elioenai; 
a brother of Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan, Delaiah and Anani. § son of the royal line of Judah

A man from the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.8.36; 
only referred to as Zimri (זִמְרִי); 
son of Jehoaddah; 
a brother of Alemeth and Azmaveth; 
father of Moza. § an obscure name mentioned in connection with 'the mingled people' in Jeremiah; may be same as 'Zimran'

A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.25.2; 
only referred to as Zimran (זִמְרָן); 
son of Abraham and Keturah; 
half-brother of: Ishmael and Isaac; 
a brother of Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak and Shuah. § the eldest son of Abraham by Keturah

A man living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at Num.25.14; 
only referred to as Zimri (זִמְרִי); 
a son of Salu. § an obscure name mentioned in connection with 'the mingled people' in Jeremiah; may be same as 'Zimran'

A man from the tribe of Judah living before Israel's Monarchy, first mentioned at Jos.7.1; 
referred to as Zabdi (זַבְדִּי), or Zimri (זִמְרִי); 
son of Zerah; 
a brother of Ethan, Heman, Calcol and Dara; 
father of Carmi. § an obscure name mentioned in connection with 'the mingled people' in Jeremiah; may be same as 'Zimran'
